<https://colonial-heritage.triply.cc/nmvw/id/object/RV-3025-76> <https://colonialcollections.nl/schema#material> "schildering op papier\r\nThe finished painting was executed on a vasli or a painting support made of a layering structure of Indian handmade paper sheets pasted together. It was done with opaque watercolour and some details were enhanced with gold paint. It is surrounded by a narrow band painted in black, a thin ruled line drawn with white ink and a larger border painted in red. Both upper and lower borders consist of two strips of paper joined to the main support. There is also another long and horizontal strip of paper pasted on the verso in the upper part.\r\nModern label at verso with title and description in Dutch of the image\r\nWorkshop traces: stains and smudges on the verso" .
